Thank you for your kind words. The updates do not appear to be aggressive enough for Travis CI and it is now a calibration task. I am restricting the CPU in Docker to 1.5 to see if I can isolate it locally.

My advice would be to use Eclipse because it supports pretty much every language. I am not going to install Eclipse and go through the process of configuring everything.

* Configure the build with the `-g` debug flag in `config/configure.ac`.
* Launch the `heron-dev` docker container.
* `docker ps` and then `docker exec -it` to open a second terminal into the `heron-dev`.
* Install `gdb` attach and set your breakpoint `-b` and watchpoints in your tests.
* Run the `stmg_unittest` in isolation.
* Good bug hunting.

